  "local_port": 43906,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What can I include in areas of interests in my resume?",
  "response": "Including areas of interest in your resume can provide potential employers with a more well-rounded view of your personality and passions. Here are some suggestions on what you can include:\n\n1. **Professional Interests**:\n   - Industry-specific trends (e.g., renewable energy, financial technology)\n   - Relevant professional organizations or groups\n   - Specialized skills or techniques (e.g., data analysis, machine learning)\n\n2. **Personal Interests**:\n   - Hobbies (e.g., photography, cooking, gardening)\n   - Sports and fitness activities (e.g., running, yoga, soccer)\n   - Arts and culture (e.g., painting, literature, theater)\n\n3. **Educational Interests**:\n   - Subjects or fields you are passionate about (e.g., psychology, history)\n   - Courses or certifications you are pursuing\n   - Areas of academic research\n\n4. **Community and Volunteering**:\n   - Volunteering activities (e.g., animal shelter, food bank)\n   - Community service projects\n   - Mentoring or coaching roles\n\n5. **Tech and Innovation**:\n   - Interest in emerging technologies (e.g., AI, blockchain)\n   - Innovation and startups\n   - Coding and programming languages\n\n6. **Travel and Exploration**:\n   - Interest in travel and different cultures\n   - Outdoor activities (e.g., hiking, camping)\n   - Adventure sports (e.g., rock climbing, scuba diving)\n\n7. **Environmental and Social Causes**:\n   - Sustainability and conservation efforts\n   - Social justice and equality initiatives\n   - Health and wellness advocacy\n\nWhen listing your areas of interest, aim to be specific and genuine. This can help spark conversation during interviews and demonstrate that you are a well-rounded individual.",
